# Retrieve data from Census Bureau
# List of country codes
country_codes = [
    '5490', # Thailand
    '5520', # Vietnam
    '5530', # Laos
    '5550', # Cambodia
    '5570', # Malaysia
    '5590', # Singapore
    '5600', # Indonesia
    '5601', # East Timor
    '5610', # Brunei
    '5650', # Philippines
    '5700', # China
    '5460'  # Burma
]

base_url = "https://www.census.gov/foreign-trade/balance/c{}.html"
all_data = []

for code in country_codes:
    full_url = base_url.format(code)
    response = requests.get(full_url)
    web_content = response.content
    soup = BeautifulSoup(web_content, "html.parser")
    tables = soup.find_all("table")

    for table in tables:
        headers = [header.text for header in table.find_all("th")]
        rows = table.find_all("tr")[1:]  # Skip header row
        data = []
        for row in rows:
            cells = [cell.text for cell in row.find_all("td")]
            if not any("TOTAL" in cell for cell in cells):
                data.append([code] + cells)  # Prepend country code to row data
        all_data.append(data)

# Convert to a single pandas DataFrame
headers = ['Country Code'] + headers  # Add the country code to headers

def clean_numeric_column(column):
    return column.str.replace(',', '').str.strip().astype(float)

merged_df['Exports'] = clean_numeric_column(merged_df['Exports'])
merged_df['Imports'] = clean_numeric_column(merged_df['Imports'])
merged_df['Balance'] = clean_numeric_column(merged_df['Balance'])

# resampling after cleaning the columns
quarterly_df = merged_df.groupby('Country Code').resample('Q').sum()
quarterly_df.reset_index(inplace=True)

# Adding SEA to the data frame
# List of SEA country codes (replace with actual codes if they are different)
sea_countries = ['Brunei', 'Cambodia', 'Indonesia', 'Laos', 'Malaysia', 'Myanmar', 
                 'Philippines', 'Singapore', 'Thailand', 'Timor-Leste', 'Vietnam','Burma']

# Filter data that is in the SEA countries list
sea_df = quarterly_df[quarterly_df['Country Code'].isin(sea_countries)]

# Aggregate the data for SEA countries
sea_aggregated = sea_df.groupby('Month').agg({'Exports': 'sum', 'Imports': 'sum', 'Balance': 'sum',
                                              'Total Trade':'sum'}).reset_index()

# Add a new column for 'Country Code' with 'SEA' as the value
sea_aggregated['Country Code'] = 'SEA'

# Append the SEA aggregated data to the original dataframe
df_sea_included = quarterly_df.append(sea_aggregated, ignore_index=True)

# Sort the dataframe based on 'Month' to maintain chronological order
quarterly_df  = df_sea_included.sort_values(by=['Month', 'Country Code'], ascending=[True, True])

# China total import from 2013-2023

# Load the dataset again to ensure we're working with the original data
# Filter data for China and the years 2013-2023
china_data = quarterly_df[(quarterly_df['Country Code'] == 'China') & 
                          (quarterly_df['Month'] >= '2013-01-01')]

# Convert 'Month' to datetime for easier handling
china_data['Month'] = pd.to_datetime(china_data['Month'])

# Group data by year and sum the imports
china_imports_by_year = china_data.groupby(china_data['Month'].dt.year)['Imports'].sum()

# Adjust the scale to millions USD from thousands (as the unit is in million dollars)
china_imports_by_year /= 1e3

# Creating the updated bar graph
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
china_imports_by_year.plot(kind='bar', color='skyblue')
plt.title('China Imports from 2013 to 2023 (in Billion USD)')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Imports (in Billion USD)')
plt.xticks(rotation=0)
plt.grid(axis='y')
plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

#Proportion of trade by each country
country_name = "Thailand"


# Convert 'Month' to datetime format and extract the year
data_sea_filtered['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data_sea_filtered['Month']).dt.year

# Filter the data for Vietnam and for years up to 2022
vietnam_data = data_sea_filtered[(data_sea_filtered['Country Code'] == country_name) 
                                 & (data_sea_filtered['Year'] >= 1995)
                                 & (data_sea_filtered['Year'] <= 2022)].copy()

# Group by the extracted year and sum the imports and exports
annual_vietnam = vietnam_data.groupby('Year')[['Imports', 'Exports']].sum()

annual_vietnam['Imports'] = annual_vietnam['Imports'] / 1000
annual_vietnam['Exports'] = annual_vietnam['Exports'] / 1000

# Creating the stacked area plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))

# Plotting the stacked area chart with the US exports to Vietnam on the bottom
annual_vietnam[['Exports', 'Imports']].plot(kind='area', stacked=True, ax=ax,
                                                          color=['lightgreen', 'skyblue'], alpha=0.5)

# Setting the title and labels
ax.set_title(f'{country_name} Trade with the US (2000-2022)')
ax.set_xlabel('Year')
ax.set_ylabel('Value in USD (billions)')
ax.legend(labels=[f'US Imports from {country_name}', f'US Exports to {country_name}'])
ax.grid(True, which='both', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)

ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MultipleLocator(2))  # Set minor ticks to every 2 year

# # Ensure x-axis ticks are displayed with the years
ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(ticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: int(x)))

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# calculating cumulative imports for each SEA country from 2000 to 2023

filtered_data_2013_2023 = data_sea_filtered[(data_sea_filtered['Month'] >= '2003')] 
#                                                  & (data_sea_filtered['Month'] <= '2023-12-31')]

# We ensure that the cumulative sum is never decreasing by taking the cumulative max
cumulative_imports_sea = filtered_data_2013_2023.groupby('Country Code')['Imports'].cumsum()

# Inserting the corrected cumulative imports back into the dataframe
quarterly_df['Cumulative Imports'] = cumulative_imports_sea.groupby(data_sea_filtered['Country Code']).cummax()

# Pivot the data to get years as columns and countries as rows for cumulative imports
pivot_cumulative_imports = quarterly_df.pivot_table(
    index='Country Code', 
    columns=quarterly_df['Month'].dt.year, 
    values='Cumulative Imports', 
    aggfunc='last'  # We take the last value of each year since it's cumulative
)

# Filling any NaNs with the previous year's data since cumulative should not decrease
pivot_cumulative_imports.fillna(method='ffill', axis=1, inplace=True)

# Generate a color map with a distinct color for each SEA country
# colors = cm.rainbow(np.linspace(0, 1, pivot_cumulative_imports.shape[0]))
colors = cm.get_cmap('tab10', pivot_cumulative_imports.shape[0])


plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))
for (country, color) in zip(pivot_cumulative_imports.index, colors.colors):
    plt.plot(pivot_cumulative_imports.columns, pivot_cumulative_imports.loc[country], 
             label=country, color=color, linestyle='-', linewidth=2)
    

plt.title('Cumulative Imports to the US from SEA Countries (1992-2023)')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Cumulative Imports (in million USD)')
plt.legend(title='Country', loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), borderaxespad=0.)
plt.grid(True)
plt.xticks(range(2000, 2024), rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()

# YoY growth rate

# Filter data for China and SEA, we're only interested in 'Imports' for growth calculation
china_imports = quarterly_df[quarterly_df['Country Code'] == 'China'].resample('A', on='Month').sum()['Imports']
sea_imports = quarterly_df[quarterly_df['Country Code'] == 'SEA'].resample('A', on='Month').sum()['Imports']


# Calculate year-over-year growth rate

china_growth = china_imports.pct_change() * 100
sea_growth = sea_imports.pct_change() * 100

# Remove the NaN values for the first year where YoY growth can't be calculated
china_growth = china_growth.dropna()
sea_growth = sea_growth.dropna()

# Create a DataFrame to hold the growth rates for plotting
growth_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Year': china_growth.index.year,
    'China Growth (%)': china_growth.values,
    'SEA Growth (%)': sea_growth.values
})

# Adjusting the DataFrame to include data from 2012 to 2022
growth_df_2012_2022 = growth_df[(growth_df['Year'] >= 2012) & (growth_df['Year'] <= 2022)]

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))
plt.bar(growth_df_2012_2022['Year'] - 0.15, growth_df_2012_2022['China Growth (%)'], 
        width=0.3, label='China Growth (%)', color='skyblue', align='center')
plt.bar(growth_df_2012_2022['Year'] + 0.15, growth_df_2012_2022['SEA Growth (%)'], 
        width=0.3, label='SEA Growth (%)', color='salmon', align='center')
plt.axhline(0, color='black', linewidth=0.5)
plt.title('Year-over-Year Growth Rates in Imports from China and SEA to the US (2012-2022)')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Growth Rate (%)')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.xticks(growth_df_2012_2022['Year'])  # Ensure all years are shown as ticks
plt.tight_layout(pad=3.0)  # Add padding to ensure the tight_layout doesn't clip the labels
plt.show()
